By Cui Huiying, southern weekly reporter

Southern weekend intern, in Beichen, Yang Learning, Song Bingchen

Editor in chief | Suping Ma

In order to control the spread of COVID-19 pneumonia, it has been a key step in the prevention and control of the epidemic to find close contacts according to the mobile route of each confirmed case and implement home isolation and observation.

Incomplete statistics showed that as of the night of January 28, at least 117 trains, 35 flights and three subway lines were "urgently looking" for the confirmed patients' fellow passengers.

Anxiety continues to escalate, but the jumbled, scattered information is not easy to query, subject to ridicule. "Why not through the real-name system ticket information directly to find passengers, but also to find people on the Internet? " Many people expressed doubts.

Many CDC staff to southern weekend reporters confirmed that the media and real-name search system is synchronized. "But the real-name system requires a lot of procedures, so the information was sent out immediately, and passengers are expected to contact us, " said a CDC official in Suzhou, some passengers without seats on the railway may walk to the car, real-name ticket purchase information is difficult to find.

Considering that it is very inconvenient to compare the tracing cards one by one, the "2019-nCoV new pneumonia patients' same itinerary query tool" developed by seven programmers was launched at 11:00 pm on January 27,2020. A developer told southern weekend that the query tool had received more than 1 million visitors within 20 hours of its launch, and the twice optimized server was still jammed.

1
Real-name search. It's reliable, but it takes time

1

###Real-name search. It's reliable, but it takes time

"The incubation period can also be contagious to others, so we need to keep him under medical observation and in relative isolation for up to 14 days of exposure. " January 25, li Lanjuan, a member of the high level Expert Group of the Chinese Academy of Engineering, said in an interview with CCTV.

When a patient is diagnosed, the retracing of his or her course of action will be officially initiated. Finding close contacts with their counterparts and monitoring the health of these "high-risk groups" is a top priority for epidemic prevention and control.

In accordance with the provisions of the second edition of the COVID-19 management programme for persons with suspected exposure to pneumonia and close contacts, who are travelling on the same mode of transport as the case and have close contacts, including those who have cared for and cared for a patient on board a vehicle; those who have accompanied the patient (family members, colleagues, friends, etc.) ; and other passengers and crew members who have been assessed as likely to have close contact with the patient, were close contacts of the case.

The Railway Department said that if fever passengers are found on the train, the local epidemic prevention departments may propose to the local railway department that the railway unit, through 12306 real-name information, find out information about the passengers in the same compartment of the fever passengers and provide it to the epidemic prevention department.

In Suzhou, for example, at 23:12 on January 26, the "Leading Group of pneumonia prevention and control of COVID-19 infection" of the Health Commission of Suzhou City issued an emergency announcement urgently looking for passengers on 16 buses of G1766 on January 22. A passenger in the train has been diagnosed. Passengers on the train are requested to call the Suzhou CDC emergency number. Duty Personnel said that the same night passengers call contact, as of 16 o'clock on the 27th, nearly 10 passengers with the CDC contact.

It is more reliable to rely on real-name ticketing information to find fellow passengers than to report them to the authorities. At 15:55 on January 25, the official website of the Pingyao County People's government issued an emergency notice saying that a confirmed case was found in the airport bus (license plate number: Jin C60695) that was traveling from Taiyuan to Pingyao at 20 p.m. on January 20, the passengers are required to report to the local village committee, Township Health Center or Community Health Service Center, and do a good job of self-isolation.

"The number of passengers found through the real-name system is relatively high, " said a local official, who said that within six hours of the announcement, all passengers had been found and had been quarantined at home.

The health department does not have the registration information of the passengers in the same compartment, the staff of the Infectious Disease Control and Prevention Institute of the Zibo Center for Disease Control and Prevention told southern weekend, the latter contact the provincial joint control and prevention mechanism units, by them responsible for finding, and finally put the relevant information back to the local. This information transfer process will take some time, although staff have been working overtime on an emergency basis.

2
Blanket tracking

2

###Blanket tracking

"We have to take our temperature twice a day and report our health status to the work unit, the sub-district office and the district CDC, " Wang Yun (not her real name) , who lives in Qingdao, told southern weekend that she was on the same flight with a confirmed patient on the 21st, he has been isolated at home for several days and has no symptoms at present, but every time he looks at the temperature test results, his heart is still very disturbed.

Wang said only 136 new cases were reported in Wuhan on January 18 and 19, "not feeling so bad. ". He bought a mask at the airport and wore it while waiting for and during the flight.

On the 25th, he suddenly received a phone call from his work unit, he needs to stay at home in isolation for half a month, do not go out. The Disease Control and prevention authorities then called him to be quarantined at home and had him take his temperature twice a day and report it. "No one told me that I had found a confirmed case on the flight I was on, but I saw it on wechat myself, " Wang recalled, he was in the front row of the plane, and the confirmed patient was in the tenth row, Far Away, and he was still worried.

Despite the evidence that not all pneumonia patients with COVID-19 have a fever, the current outbreak is dominated by a small thermometer. Grass-roots communities are being mobilized after 30 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities directly under the Central Government) launched a first-level response to public health emergencies. Each person's temperature and health information will be flattened into a single report in the table.

On January 27, the National Health Commission said at a press conference that the current epidemic prevention and control is at a critical moment, it is necessary to give full play to the mobilization capacity of grass-roots communities, including rural communities. Carpet-like tracking, grid-based management is moving forward.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A worker disinfects security equipment at the Line 2, Xi'an Metro West Station in Daming Palace January 27,2010. (Zhang Bowen, Xinhua News Agency)

In order to find "high-risk groups" such as returnees from Wuhan and close contacts of patients, in addition to publishing information on the epidemic in the media to find relevant passengers of the same trade, local governments have also gone out of their way to cover up the omission, and the tracking information is more detailed.

On January 28, Shijiazhuang, Hebei Province, offered a reward of 2,000 yuan for anyone who failed to register for returning from Wuhan; Yangquan, Shanxi Province, even began looking for residents and washers who took baths in the men's bathhouse of the City Government Bathing Center from 14:30 to 17:00 on January 22, because a confirmed patient once showered here.

3
To what extent are "close contacts" ?

3

###To what extent are "close contacts" ?

Southern weekend reporters found that most of the information looking for fellow passengers was sent by the Terminal City, but few of the stops along the way were informed.

Anhui Province local media "Xin 'an evening news" from January 25 began to publish confirmed patients with the vehicle information, as of January 27, a total of seven trains, buses and other information. Southern weekend reporters collated and found that six of the train through Fuyang, Lu'an, Bozhou, Hefei and other cities in Anhui, the terminal are not in Anhui Province, a bus ride. "Xin 'an evening news" reporter told that the train information is based on local health commission information and other areas of the report (such as the train stops in Anhui Province) self-collation.

Southern weekend reporters searched the website of the Anhui Provincial Health Commission and found no information about finding fellow passengers. According to the original report provided by the provincial CDC contact, southern weekend reporter 27 evening contact duty personnel, said it did not receive the request to collect patient passenger information.

There is no uniform standard for how large a range of fellow passengers should be classified as "close contacts" .

A CDC official in Suzhou told southern weekend, "The internal guidelines only require that we look for passengers in the same row and in the front and back rows, but we've expanded the scope to the entire carriage, so if you're not in the same carriage as the patient, you don't have to worry. "

The Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region has designated passengers on entire trains or flights as "suspicious objects" . At 20:47 on January 27, the Guangxi Health Commission issued an emergency notice saying that 23 patients had traveled to many parts of Guangxi by seven trains and eight flights between January 13 and 22, with a total of 5,594 passengers on the same journey.

After the southern weekend reporter contacted the Guangxi Health Commission, the staff explained that the air circulation in the train or plane was poor, and patients might also move around in different carriages. "New coronavirus pneumonia" was mainly transmitted by respiratory droplets, it can also be transmitted through contact. It may also happen if fellow passengers come into contact with objects contaminated by the infected person and touch the nose and mouth.

Lu Jiahai, a professor at the National Sun Yat-sen University's public health, said it was "necessary to take such measures" to minimize the spread of the disease.

4
Torn right to know and right to privacy

4

###Torn right to know and right to privacy

On January 26,2020, Wuhan's mayor, Zhou Xianwang, announced at a news conference that figures were disturbing as more than five million people left the city because of the Spring Festival and the outbreak. The number of fellow passengers in Wuhan, whether someone has been diagnosed, has become a "just need" to alleviate anxiety.

January 27 at 11:00 pm, by seven programmers to build the "2019-nCoV new pneumonia confirmed patients with the same itinerary query tool" officially launched. Enter your vehicle, time and location to find out if you were traveling with someone who was diagnosed.

One of the programmers told southern weekend that less than a day on-line, the traffic has exceeded 1 million, "the server is almost unbearable, we have been optimizing. ".

In most cases, the spread of the virus is not intentional, but the "malevolence" against Wuhan people and even the entire Hubei people is spreading, and the public's right to know and the patient's right to privacy are torn.

A passenger confirmed that the flight was called "air dropped virus" by netizens. Before the diagnosis, the patients who had taken multiple subway lines in Nanjing and Qingdao on their return journey were also scolded on Weibo Wuhan has a travel history of the citizens or returned students with information statistics, personal information on the blink of an eye was leaked to the Internet, encounter human flesh search or as a "potential virus. ".

Since the outbreak, about January 20, the health commission in all provinces began to release through the official website of the epidemic notification. It was noted that some of the notifications were detailed and timely, but revealed information such as the patient's last name, place of employment, town of residence and so on, which could easily lead to the identification of individuals.

"Some people do not report their own work unit, first to investigate the address, telephone and travel history, feeling that my information was leaked, has been reported to the police. " But did not report the health information as required.

"The disclosure of the personal information of these close contacts should be held accountable, " said Zheng Lei, a professor at the School of International Relations and Public Affairs and Director of the digital and Mobile Governance Laboratory at Fudan University.

As things stand, there are no clear standards for what information should be made public and what should be protected, and processing and the degree of disclosure vary from place to place. "generally speaking, the personal information and work units of the confirmed patients should not be too specific, and People's names, ID card numbers and telephone numbers can not be listed, " Zheng told southern weekend.
